cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Sentinel: observability and trust layer for AI agents"
message: "If you use Sentinel in your research or product, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "The Sentinel Authors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/SumanD18/sentinel"
url: "https://github.com/SumanD18/sentinel"
abstract: >-
  Sentinel is an open-source, self-hostable observability and trust layer for
  LLM pipelines and agents. It traces every prompt, tool call, and retrieval,
  estimates cost, and scores outputs with local-first evaluators to flag
  hallucinations, runaway loops, and silent failures.
keywords:
  - observability
  - large language models
  - ai agents
  - tracing
  - evaluation
  - hallucination detection
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.1.1
date-released: "2026-05-31"
